  Bonus Video: Simple Video-to-Video Workflows

In this lesson, we're going to shake things up a bit and look at a few video-to-video workflows. Video-to-video is very powerful and represents an entirely new and effective way to convert footage to different styles using AI technology.

  • Download the Assets
  • Link to Runway

  • Ebsynth

Links to Interesting Projects (With Application):

  • Cardboard to Scene (Previs)
  • Gen 1 Landing Page (Stylization and 3D Model to Stylized Result)
  • Martin Haerlin (Change the Character)
  • Anime Rock, Paper, Scissors (Video Conversion)

Some Quick Tips:

  • Character faces will break down when they turn away from the camera.
  • Always use preview styles before rendering to save on time and credits.
  • If a video breaks down too much, try adjusting the frame consistency slider. Add more for stability and less for creative interpretation on tricky scenes.
  • Structural consistency should be low. I don't recommend turning it up.
  • Always upres inside Topaz Video AI afterward before you start editing. You need the improvement in quality.

My Ideal Runway Gen 1 Settings (Typically):

  • Structural Consistency: 1
  • Style Weight: 10-15
  • Frame Consistency: 1.75
